name: disable-android-websocket-reconnect-loop-fix
description: This flag acts as a killswitch for a fix related to the Android client websocket connection. The changes that were made removed some old automatic refresh logic that was causing an issue where the websocket could get stuck in a reconnecting loop. Turning this flag on disables the fix, and re-introduces the old automatic refresh/reconnect logic.

name: Automatically flag profile on login
description: This feature gate allows us to automatically flag certain profiles when they log in. This is useful in cases where there's a problem in a given country or region, and our flagging systems are not able to identify the bad actors. It's easier to just automatically flag everybody and then have AI moderators review the flags and remove the bad actors.
